# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:50
translate spanish hwb_s02_b39ddbf9:

    # "A pleasant little chime greets me as I enter the station, Marina trailing closely behind."
    "Un agradable tintineo me recibe al entrar a la estación, con Marina siguiéndome de cerca."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:52
translate spanish hwb_s02_1732353f:

    # "The drive was quiet after I turned the music on. Turning the tables on her and asking what she was doing out there seemed to throw off her."
    "El viaje fue tranquilo después de que encendí la música. Darle la vuelta a la situación y preguntarle qué hacía allí pareció desconcertarla."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:54
translate spanish hwb_s02_63048ab3:

    # "I didn’t mean to come off as cold as I did."
    "No quise sonar tan fría como lo hice."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:56
translate spanish hwb_s02_641aebe0:

    # "It’s just been ages since I’ve had a conversation beyond accepting some half-hearted condolences. Though to be fair, I haven’t really wanted to hold one."
    "Ha pasado una eternidad desde que tuve una conversación más allá de aceptar algunas condolencias a medias. Aunque, para ser justa, tampoco es que haya querido tener una."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:58
translate spanish hwb_s02_e89e68f1:

    # "The guy behind the counter is busy ringing someone up, so I set out in search of a gas can."
    "El tipo detrás del mostrador está ocupado cobrando a alguien, así que me pongo a buscar un bidón de gasolina."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:60
translate spanish hwb_s02_959e22e9:

    # "The store is one of those big mini-mart places, made specifically for travelers. It’s surprisingly clean for a place surrounded by sand. Every corner has an unnatural, sanitary shine accompanied by the scent of citrus cleaning product."
    "La tienda es de esas grandes de mini-súper, hechas específicamente para viajeros. Es sorprendentemente limpia para un lugar rodeado de arena. Cada rincón tiene un brillo sanitario antinatural, acompañado del olor a limpiador cítrico."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:69
translate spanish hwb_s02_f1e9ba50:

    # Marina "Hey, they have the cola flavor here!"
    Marina "Эй, у них есть коктейль со вкусом колы!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:71
translate spanish hwb_s02_d748098b:

    # "I turn and find Marina clutching the slushie machine, her eyes widening like a cat’s when tempted with yarn."
    "Me giro y encuentro a Marina abrazando la máquina de slushie, con los ojos abiertos como los de un gato cuando lo tientan con un ovillo de lana."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:77
translate spanish hwb_s02_2d70af9f:

    # Amber "Don’t most gas stations have it?"
    Amber "Разве он не на всех заправках есть?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:79
translate spanish hwb_s02_4ae1f262:

    # "She shakes her head, but doesn't take her eyes off of the machine."
    "Ella niega con la cabeza, pero no aparta la mirada de la máquina."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:81
translate spanish hwb_s02_85d1e4eb:

    # Marina "Uh-uh."
    Marina "Не-а."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:86
translate spanish hwb_s02_64df7fb6:

    # Marina "All the places back home only had cherry and raspberry. When we got sick of them, we just had to mix them together."
    Marina "Дома везде были только вишневые и клубничные. Когда они надоели, мы начали их смешивать."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:95
translate spanish hwb_s02_db1915f0:

    # Marina "But…"
    Marina "Но..."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:97
translate spanish hwb_s02_b4b14a5b:

    # "Marina finally turns to me, wearing a face of pure, concentrated sadness."
    "Marina finalmente se vuelve hacia mí, con una cara de pura y concentrada tristeza."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:103
translate spanish hwb_s02_e2a3c3f5:

    # Marina "I left my wallet in my car."
    Marina "Я забыла кошелек в машине."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:105
translate spanish hwb_s02_85f11447:

    # "It’s the saddest thing I’ve ever seen. Just looking at her, I can feel my heart brea—wait a second."
    "Es lo más triste que he visto en mi vida. Solo con mirarla, siento que mi corazón se romp—espera un segundo."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:110
translate spanish hwb_s02_f8853593:

    # Amber "How were you expecting to pay for the gas?"
    Amber "И как ты собиралась расплачиваться за бензин?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:115
translate spanish hwb_s02_6d99eef5:

    # Marina "I-I don’t know. I just remembered."
    Marina "Я-я не знаю. Я только вспомнила."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:120
translate spanish hwb_s02_14cfef9d:

    # "How did she last five minutes out in the desert?"
    "¿Cómo es que duró cinco minutos en el desierto?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:125
translate spanish hwb_s02_62cbb7ff:

    # Amber "Fine, I guess I’ll pay for it."
    Amber "Ладно, я заплачу за тебя."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:130
translate spanish hwb_s02_6ef7be50:

    # Marina "R-Really?"
    Marina "П-правда?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:135
translate spanish hwb_s02_475c2dad:

    # Amber "Yeah, yeah. And grab yourself one of those slushies, too."
    Amber "Да, да. И коктейль себе возьми."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:140
translate spanish hwb_s02_52a5d329:

    # Amber "But make it a small one."
    Amber "Но только маленький."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:145
translate spanish hwb_s02_19bbfe48:

    # "Her pure, concentrated sadness melts into pure, unconcentrated happiness."
    "Su pura y concentrada tristeza se derrite en pura y desconcentrada felicidad."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:147
translate spanish hwb_s02_dae1cd82:

    # Marina "You’re the best, Amber!"
    Marina "Ты лучшая, Эмбер!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:159
translate spanish hwb_s02_d2e9c555:

    # "She grabs a cup and holds down the button until the slushie overflows and drips down the side."
    "Toma un vaso y presiona el botón hasta que el slushie se desborda y gotea por el costado."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:166
translate spanish hwb_s02_ff5ef5d0:

    # "I was going to pay for the gas anyway, but I’m hoping the drink makes up for the drive over."
    "De todas formas iba a pagar la gasolina, pero espero que la bebida compense el viaje en coche."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:168
translate spanish hwb_s02_8f583664:

    # "I spot the gas cans, and with Marina happily sipping from a straw, grab one and head for the counter."
    "Veo los bidones de gasolina, y con Marina sorbiendo felizmente de un popote, agarro uno y me dirijo al mostrador."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:190
translate spanish hwb_s02_6423d3e1:

    # "The guy at the register is still ringing up the same girl. Lines of flimsy plastic bags line the counter, filled with a mixture of off-brand junk food and gardening tools."
    "El tipo de la caja registradora sigue cobrando a la misma chica. Hileras de bolsas de plástico endebles bordean el mostrador, llenas de una mezcla de comida chatarra de marca genérica y herramientas de jardinería."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:192
translate spanish hwb_s02_90a24397:

    # "He scans the items as the girl digs through her wallet, her bandana-wrapped head pressing a phone against her shoulder."
    "Escanea los artículos mientras la chica hurga en su cartera, con la cabeza envuelta en un pañuelo presionando un teléfono contra su hombro."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:197
translate spanish hwb_s02_71a7aaeb:

    # BandanaGirl "Aren't you supposed to be the badass mechanic? What good are you if you're not?"
    BandanaGirl "Разве не ты у нас должен быть крутым механиком? Какая от тебя иначе польза?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:199
translate spanish hwb_s02_a2f19472:

    # "She swipes out a card and hands it to the cashier, more interested in staring at her nails than looking at him."
    "Saca una tarjeta y se la entrega al cajero, más interesada en mirarse las uñas que en mirarlo a él."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:203
translate spanish hwb_s02_a1310649:

    # BandanaGirl "How the hell would I know? Have the squirt check underneath it if you're so curious."
    BandanaGirl "С какого хрена я должна знать? Посмотри, не течет ли из нее что-то снизу, если тебе так интересно."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:205
translate spanish hwb_s02_71a72d8f:

    # "On the other end of the line, I can hear the faintest of squabbling. I can't make out anything they're saying, but the tone sounds worlds more tolerable than the girl's."
    "Del otro lado de la línea, puedo oír una discusión muy leve. No logro distinguir lo que dicen, pero el tono suena muchísimo más tolerable que el de la chica."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:209
translate spanish hwb_s02_11f789d5:

    # BandanaGirl "If it's that old then I say do it. Cash is cash. It's not like anyone's gonna care."
    BandanaGirl "Если она такая старая, то вперед! Деньги есть деньги. Не думаю, что кому-то есть до нее дело."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:213
translate spanish hwb_s02_ab3b9d61:

    # BandanaGirl "You better not take as long as last time though! I’ll be waiting for you slackers outside."
    BandanaGirl "Только давай чуть быстрее, чем в прошлый раз, понял? Жду вас снаружи, спиногрызы."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:217
translate spanish hwb_s02_83b1758e:

    # "The girl slips her phone back into the crevices of her dangerously unzipped jumpsuit. What little clothing she has on underneath looks like it's going to burst from the slightest movement."
    "La chica desliza su teléfono de vuelta en los pliegues de su mono peligrosamente desabrochado. La poca ropa que lleva debajo parece que va a reventar con el más mínimo movimiento."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:219
translate spanish hwb_s02_6505740f:

    # "Not my type, especially with that personality, but it's hard for me to do anything other than stare."
    "No es mi tipo, especialmente con esa personalidad, pero me cuesta hacer otra cosa que no sea mirar."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:225
translate spanish hwb_s02_18ecb018:

    # "The attendant reaches out to help with the bags, but the girl snaps them away before he can. She shoots him with a heated glare that burns straight through the man and into the wall behind him."
    "El dependiente extiende la mano para ayudar con las bolsas, pero la chica las arrebata antes de que pueda hacerlo. Le lanza una mirada ardiente que atraviesa al hombre y se clava en la pared detrás de él."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:229
translate spanish hwb_s02_32b59f89:

    # "Turning around, the girl looks at us for a second before rolling her eyes, then marches out the door, the bags weighing her down as they nearly scrape the ground."
    "Al darse la vuelta, la chica nos mira un segundo antes de poner los ojos en blanco, y luego sale marchando por la puerta, con las bolsas pesándole mientras casi rozan el suelo."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:248
translate spanish hwb_s02_9c716c6d:

    # "Yeah, definitely not my type."
    "Sí, definitivamente no es mi tipo."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:252
translate spanish hwb_s02_e8585ef1:

    # Attendant "Good luck!"
    Attendant "Счастливо!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:254
translate spanish hwb_s02_39632dc6:

    # "Marina and I set the can and nearly empty slushie on the counter."
    "Marina y yo colocamos el bidón y el slushie casi vacío sobre el mostrador."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:261
translate spanish hwb_s02_a9d1179f:

    # Attendant "Will that be all?"
    Attendant "У вас все?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:266
translate spanish hwb_s02_b6ba5d01:

    # Amber "Yeah. Sorry if we're more boring than that other girl."
    Amber "Ага. Извините, что мы скучнее той девушки."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:270
translate spanish hwb_s02_0445e64d:

    # "The attendant hacks out a dry cackle and scans the gas can. He flicks his oily ponytail behind his shoulder, and then rings up Marina's drink."
    "El dependiente suelta una risa seca y escanea el bidón de gasolina. Se echa su grasienta coleta detrás del hombro, y luego cobra la bebida de Marina."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:272
translate spanish hwb_s02_6d7856d4:

    # Attendant "Been a lot of folks passin' through and stockin' up the past few days."
    Attendant "В последние несколько дней много народу проезжает мимо и затаривается."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:276
translate spanish hwb_s02_d7bda686:

    # Attendant "It's been a good change of pace."
    Attendant "Это приятное разнообразие."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:280
translate spanish hwb_s02_c4524a40:

    # Attendant "I’m guessin’ that’s why you girls are here too?"
    Attendant "Я полагаю, вы, девчонки, здесь по той же причине, что и все?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:291
translate spanish hwb_s02_32a5b7e9:

    # "Marina eases in towards the counter, nudging herself tightly between me and a rack, her hands creeping over to the slushie."
    "Marina se acerca al mostrador, metiéndose apretadamente entre yo y un estante, con las manos deslizándose hacia el slushie."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:294
translate spanish hwb_s02_853c25ae:

    # Amber "Can’t say I follow you. I’m just heading out to California or any place. Everyone's a drum major leading a parade of hurts, marching with our bitterness."
    Amber "Не совсем понимаю, о чем вы. Я просто еду в Калифорнию, или куда-нибудь еще. Я — ведущий парада боли, марширующий в ногу с огорчением."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:298
translate spanish hwb_s02_de23376d:

    # "The attendant freezes, leaving the tank unscanned. Blinding red light beams from the scanner."
    "El dependiente se congela, dejando el tanque sin escanear. Una luz roja cegadora emana del escáner."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:300
translate spanish hwb_s02_76521b7e:

    # Attendant "You uh... got a farm you left behind in Oklahoma or something?"
    Attendant "У тебя... У тебя там ферма осталась в Оклахоме, или что?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:305
translate spanish hwb_s02_d77c2d69:

    # Amber "Nope. That would mean something. It doesn't take nerve to do something when there's nothing else you can do."
    Amber "Нет. Это бы здорово все осложнило. А сейчас мне ничего другого не остается."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:309
translate spanish hwb_s02_c7851667:

    # Attendant "You seriously need a hobby. How about looking for the treasure like everyone else?"
    Attendant "Тебе определенно стоит подыскать себе какое-нибудь хобби. Например, искать клад, как все остальные."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:313
translate spanish hwb_s02_586f5b88:

    # Amber "For what? I’m just heading out to California."
    Amber "Зачем? Я просто еду в Калифорнию."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:315
translate spanish hwb_s02_bf21feb3:

    # "If I don’t end up driving myself insane first."
    "Si no termino volviéndome loca primero."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:319
translate spanish hwb_s02_69accae9:

    # Attendant "Ya mean ya don’t know?"
    Attendant "Хошь сказать, ты не в курсе?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:323
translate spanish hwb_s02_bcb53bed:

    # "The attendant freezes, forgetting about the scanner in his hand. Blinding red light beams from it onto my chest."
    "El empleado se queda paralizado, olvidándose del escáner en su mano. Un cegador rayo de luz roja se proyecta desde él hacia mi pecho."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:328
translate spanish hwb_s02_6f839ac4:

    # Amber "About what?"
    Amber "О чем?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:332
translate spanish hwb_s02_2bf7c870:

    # Attendant "Why, the treasure!"
    Attendant "О сокровище конечно!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:334
translate spanish hwb_s02_6f686e6b:

    # "Marina’s hands stop just shy of grabbing the cup."
    "Las manos de Marina se detienen justo antes de agarrar la taza."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:341
translate spanish hwb_s02_658fce2a:

    # Amber "...Treasure?"
    Amber "... Сокровище?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:343
translate spanish hwb_s02_2dbd0597:

    # "The clerk's chubby face morphs into a grin."
    "El rostro regordete del dependiente se transforma en una sonrisa."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:345
translate spanish hwb_s02_50eff2dd:

    # Attendant "Ya telling me that you girls haven’t heard of the treasure and the journal?"
    Attendant "Вы че, хотите сказать, что не слышали о сокровище и дневнике?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:349
translate spanish hwb_s02_3bdd92d6:

    # Marina "I have!"
    Marina "Я слышала!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:357
translate spanish hwb_s02_e2dd5393:

    # "I frown. Embarrassed, Marina looks at the floor again, her cheeks flushing red."
    "Frunzo el ceño. Avergonzada, Marina vuelve a mirar al suelo, con las mejillas sonrojadas."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:359
translate spanish hwb_s02_0673ea6f:

    # "I guess she's always just this forward."
    "Supongo que siempre es así de directa."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:369
translate spanish hwb_s02_5938ca74:

    # Marina "Well, I heard about it on the news."
    Marina "Ну, я слышала в новостях."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:373
translate spanish hwb_s02_f2566db3:

    # Marina "It's kind of why I drove down here..."
    Marina "И вот поэтому я сюда и поехала..."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:377
translate spanish hwb_s02_adac24fa:

    # Amber "You drove out into the middle of the desert for... treasure?"
    Amber "Ты поехала в сердце пустыни ради... сокровища?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:381
translate spanish hwb_s02_6d1c6c9d:

    # Amber "Sorry, but you’ve lost me."
    Amber "Прости, но это чересчур."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:385
translate spanish hwb_s02_baa09115:

    # Attendant "Not just any treasure, missy—the Miner’s Treasure!"
    Attendant "Не просто сокровище, дорогуша, — Сокровище Старателя!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:387
translate spanish hwb_s02_e6e7e7f4:

    # "He says it like that should clarify what he meant."
    "Lo dice como si eso aclarara lo que quiso decir."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:393
translate spanish hwb_s02_e3a5312e:

    # "I stare at him."
    "Lo miro fijamente."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:395
translate spanish hwb_s02_42f192bf:

    # "He stares back."
    "Él me devuelve la mirada."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:399
translate spanish hwb_s02_889283a4:

    # "Marina sips the last dregs of her slushie."
    "Marina bebe los últimos restos de su granizado."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:403
translate spanish hwb_s02_b8721223:

    # Attendant "Ya honestly don’t know?"
    Attendant "Да ты че, правда не знаешь?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:407
translate spanish hwb_s02_7e422165:

    # Amber "Not a clue. Are you gonna change that?"
    Amber "Понятия не имею. Просветишь?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:409
translate spanish hwb_s02_416a175d:

    # Attendant "Lil' feisty, ain't ya?"
    Attendant "Погляди, какая шустрая!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:411
translate spanish hwb_s02_e1e32323:

    # Amber "Not really. Just have stuff to do."
    Amber "Не особо. Просто дела есть."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:415
translate spanish hwb_s02_1c27fb7f:

    # Attendant "Fair 'nuff."
    Attendant "Само собой."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:421
translate spanish hwb_s02_9971c412:

    # Attendant "A little while back, some folks were going through all the trash in their garage."
    Attendant "Некоторое время назад какие-то ребята разбирали хлам в своем гараже."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:423
translate spanish hwb_s02_d7d92df3:

    # Attendant "As fate would have it, they came across an old journal."
    Attendant "И судьба распорядилась так, что там они нашли старый дневник."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:425
translate spanish hwb_s02_acc2d53e:

    # Attendant "Turns out, the thing belonged to their great uncle—or maybe it was their great grandfather—I don’t know. Some dead old ma-"
    Attendant "Оказывается, он принадлежал их прадеду, или типа пра-прадеду. Короче, какому-то мертвому стари—"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:436
translate spanish hwb_s02_477276f8:

    # "I cut him off with a cough, a polite hint for him to either get on with it or quit his yammering."
    "Lo interrumpo con una tos, un leve indicio para que se apresure o deje de divagar."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:438
translate spanish hwb_s02_5ecb9efb:

    # "Despite apparently knowing all this, Marina continues to with rapt attention. Sometimes her drink makes that annoying slurping sound again."
    "A pesar de saber aparentemente todo esto, Marina sigue escuchando con atención. A veces, su bebida hace ese molesto sonido de sorber otra vez."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:442
translate spanish hwb_s02_3d326307:

    # Attendant "Sorry, I’ll try keepin’ it short."
    Attendant "Прости, постараюсь покороче."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:446
translate spanish hwb_s02_4641e555:

    # Attendant "Anyway, after flippin’ through it, they found out that he'd struck it rich during the gold rush."
    Attendant "В общем, они его пролистали и поняли, что мужик неплохо заработал во время золотой лихорадки."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:450
translate spanish hwb_s02_6bb01a26:

    # Amber "If he \"struck it rich\" then wouldn’t the family know about it? They’d have to be pretty well off, right?"
    Amber "Если он “неплохо заработал”, то его семья должна была бы быть в курсе, так ведь? Они наверное довольно богаты, нет?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:454
translate spanish hwb_s02_aa987a68:

    # Marina "Oh, I can answer that!"
    Marina "Ой, я знаю!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:460
translate spanish hwb_s02_9e84e915:

    # Marina "He went back home to Missouri without {i}any{/i} gold and told all his friends he hid it!"
    Marina "Он вернулся домой в Миссури вообще {i}без золота{/i} и сказал друзьям, что спрятал его."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:464
translate spanish hwb_s02_9706e6d3:

    # "By now, the slushie is all gone. Marina tries for one last sip, but all that's sucked through the straw is air. She peers down into the cup and blows out a small sigh."
    "Para entonces, el granizado se ha acabado. Marina intenta dar un último sorbo, pero todo lo que pasa por el popote es aire. Mira dentro del vaso y exhala un pequeño suspiro."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:466
translate spanish hwb_s02_75aff41a:

    # Marina "No one believed him, though..."
    Marina "Но ему никто не поверил..."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:470
translate spanish hwb_s02_65d76b6b:

    # "I raise an eyebrow. If even this girl knows about it then I must be more out of the loop than I thought."
    "Levanto una ceja. Si hasta esta chica lo sabe, entonces debo estar más fuera de onda de lo que pensaba."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:474
translate spanish hwb_s02_d6c47279:

    # Attendant "Well now, looks like sister here's been doin' her research."
    Attendant "Похоже, малая неплохо подготовилась, да?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:478
translate spanish hwb_s02_1bdca53b:

    # Marina "Mhm!"
    Marina "Угу!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:480
translate spanish hwb_s02_2adbecb4:

    # "The attendant leans into the counter and smirks."
    "El empleado se inclina sobre el mostrador y sonríe con suficiencia."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:484
translate spanish hwb_s02_b2362bac:

    # Attendant "Story goes, he wanted to eventually move his family out West and dig his gold back up along the way, but kicked it before he could."
    Attendant "Слухи ходят, что он хотел со своей семьей уехать на Запад и по пути прихватить закопанное золотишко, но внезапно сыграл в ящик."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:488
translate spanish hwb_s02_a74c779b:

    # "He slides his thumb along his neck and makes a cheesy sound effect to go with it. Marina giggles, but I just keep staring."
    "Desliza su pulgar por su cuello y hace un efecto de sonido cursi para acompañarlo. Marina se ríe, pero yo solo sigo mirando."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:494
translate spanish hwb_s02_9008b8af:

    # Attendant "The folks that found the journal ended up selling it to some hotshot publishin’ house. Now everyone wants to retrace his steps and find the treasure."
    Attendant "Те люди, что нашли дневник, в итоге продали его в какое-то крупное издательство. Теперь его историю узнали все и само собой хотят найти сокровище, следуя по стопам старика."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:496
translate spanish hwb_s02_ffd8fe74:

    # Attendant "Shipments have been sellin' like hotcakes. Just got ours last week."
    Attendant "Книжки разлетаются как горячие пирожки. Нам вот тоже пришла партия на прошлой неделе."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:498
translate spanish hwb_s02_d869ccec:

    # "He points to a rack of identical books sitting by the door. A sign hanging above it reads {i}Treasure of the Desert: A Miner’s Journey - Take Part in the New Gold Rush!{/i}"
    "Señala un estante de libros idénticos junto a la puerta. Un letrero colgado arriba dice: {i}Tesoro del Desierto: El Viaje de un Minero - ¡Sé Parte de la Nueva Fiebre del Oro!{/i}"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:500
translate spanish hwb_s02_4c5fa9e1:

    # "Yeah, that’ll stick in people’s heads."
    "Sí, eso se quedará grabado en la mente de la gente."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:504
translate spanish hwb_s02_11a62341:

    # Amber "And people are really buying into this?"
    Amber "И что, все на это купились?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:508
translate spanish hwb_s02_c30c0883:

    # Attendant "Sure are. I’ve worked here for over twenty years, and never have I seen this many people passing through."
    Attendant "Еще как. Я здесь двадцать лет работаю, но такой толпы приезжих не видел."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:510
translate spanish hwb_s02_b69a8444:

    # Attendant "Even the banshee before you was here for some supplies and a journal."
    Attendant "Даже ведьмочка перед вами покупала припасы и дневник."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:514
translate spanish hwb_s02_fbb3b93f:

    # "Sure, okay. This is a hoax if I’ve ever seen one."
    "Claro, está bien. Esto es un engaño si alguna vez vi uno."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:516
translate spanish hwb_s02_51050670:

    # Amber "And where is this supposed treasure?"
    Amber "И где находится это “сокровище”?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:518
translate spanish hwb_s02_dc7b166e:

    # Attendant "No one knows."
    Attendant "Никто не знает."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:520
translate spanish hwb_s02_c86ff309:

    # Attendant "It’s all scattered around the desert. They say the journal has hints to its whereabouts."
    Attendant "Оно разбросано по пустыне. Говорят, только в дневнике можно найти подсказки о том, как его найти."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:524
translate spanish hwb_s02_b0b540e0:

    # Amber "Uh-huuuuh."
    Amber "Ясно."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:528
translate spanish hwb_s02_9ea9c4a5:

    # Amber "Marina, you said this is why you drove out here?"
    Amber "Марина, ты говорила, что приехала сюда именно по этой причине?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:532
translate spanish hwb_s02_008de190:

    # Marina "Yep! That’s right!"
    Marina "Ага! Так точно!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:536
translate spanish hwb_s02_bbe5fb67:

    # Amber "But you don’t really believe the treasure exists, do you?"
    Amber "Но ты ведь не веришь, что это сокровище и правда существует, да?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:540
translate spanish hwb_s02_09f224f8:

    # Marina "Sure I do!"
    Marina "Еще как верю!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:544
translate spanish hwb_s02_06c884fb:

    # "She pauses to think."
    "Ella se detiene a pensar."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:548
translate spanish hwb_s02_d4283e2e:

    # Marina "At least, I want to."
    Marina "По крайней мере, я хочу верить."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:552
translate spanish hwb_s02_c426c2a4:

    # Marina "But wouldn't it be super cool if there was treasure?"
    Marina "Ведь было бы супер круто, если бы сокровище реально существовало, да?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:556
translate spanish hwb_s02_41ee26ed:

    # Amber "Sure it would be cool…"
    Amber "Конечно, было бы круто..."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:560
translate spanish hwb_s02_109d6f2d:

    # Amber "But there's a good chance it isn't. And even if it were, do you know where to start looking?"
    Amber "Но есть большая вероятность, что это не так. Ну, допустим, оно есть, ты хоть представляешь, где следует начать его поиски?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:564
translate spanish hwb_s02_e230df89:

    # Marina "No... Not really. I never got that far. I don't even have a copy of the journal."
    Marina "Нет, на самом деле... Я никогда еще об этом не думала. У меня даже этого дневника нет."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:566
translate spanish hwb_s02_2448f679:

    # "She lowers her head, like she knows there's a good chance what I'm saying is true."
    "Baja la cabeza, como si supiera que hay una gran posibilidad de que lo que digo sea cierto."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:570
translate spanish hwb_s02_b2aaa74e:

    # Marina "But I have to try."
    Marina "Но я должна попытаться."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:572
translate spanish hwb_s02_99785cd0:

    # "Her voice is soft and quiet, but there's a faint glow of determination behind it. It makes me feel ashamed for scolding, but the idea that she dropped everything for {i}treasure{/i} is insane."
    "Su voz es suave y tranquila, pero hay un tenue brillo de determinación detrás. Me hace sentir vergüenza por regañarla, pero la idea de que dejara todo por {i}un tesoro{/i} es una locura."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:576
translate spanish hwb_s02_e1176fb1:

    # "To her credit, she did \"a little research,\" but that's cancelled out by driving into the desert without a full tank of gas. She wasn't prepared at all."
    "Para su crédito, hizo \"una pequeña investigación\", pero eso se anula al conducir al desierto sin el tanque lleno de gasolina. No estaba preparada en absoluto."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:580
translate spanish hwb_s02_0cbd3782:

    # "The people who care about her must be worried sick. I barely even know her and {i}I'm{/i} worried."
    "Las personas que se preocupan por ella deben estar preocupadísimas. Apenas la conozco y {i}yo{/i} estoy preocupada."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:588
translate spanish hwb_s02_0f67620c:

    # Attendant "Aww, don’t be too hard on her, missy. After all, who can resist a good treasure hunt?"
    Attendant "Ох, не серчай на нее, дорогуша. В конце концов, кто может устоять перед поиском сокровищ?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:592
translate spanish hwb_s02_745e4b8e:

    # "He looks to Marina and gives a big gummy grin, courtesy of his missing teeth."
    "Mira a Marina y le dedica una gran sonrisa desdentada, cortesía de sus dientes faltantes."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:596
translate spanish hwb_s02_30696d99:

    # Attendant "Ain’t that right, sister?"
    Attendant "Не правда ли, сестренка?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:600
translate spanish hwb_s02_d84f562f:

    # "Marina springs back with a smile of her own."
    "Marina retrocede con una sonrisa propia."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:602
translate spanish hwb_s02_cfc5b12a:

    # Marina "That’s right!"
    Marina "Правда!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:606
translate spanish hwb_s02_ce44cdac:

    # "Rolling my eyes, I reach into my pocket and pass some crumpled bills to the clerk."
    "Rodando los ojos, meto la mano en el bolsillo y le paso unos billetes arrugados al empleado."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:610
translate spanish hwb_s02_93219ae3:

    # Amber "Yeah, well, I’ll believe when I see it."
    Amber "Ну да... Поверю, когда сама увижу."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:614
translate spanish hwb_s02_c513e0a0:

    # "He shrugs and stuffs the cash in the register, though now I’m just paying for the tank and an empty cup. I pocket the change."
    "Él se encoge de hombros y mete el efectivo en la caja registradora, aunque ahora solo estoy pagando por el tanque y un vaso vacío. Me guardo el cambio."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:624
translate spanish hwb_s02_387a6279:

    # "I give a casual wave from the exit—that should be a good enough thank you."
    "Desde la salida, hago un gesto casual con la mano; eso debería bastar como agradecimiento."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:626
translate spanish hwb_s02_894ae24d:

    # "Marina follows, though a bit more animated, waving her arm like a fan as she says goodbye."
    "Marina me sigue, aunque un poco más animada, moviendo el brazo como un abanico mientras se despide."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:631
translate spanish hwb_s02_d73963f9:

    # Attendant "Oh, and sister!"
    Attendant "Эй, сестренка!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:636
translate spanish hwb_s02_49341fc0:

    # Marina "Yeah?"
    Marina "Да?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:641
translate spanish hwb_s02_49442181:

    # Attendant "You go ahead and take one of them journals."
    Attendant "Возьми-ка себе один из этих дневников."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:645
translate spanish hwb_s02_d28c0eb3:

    # Attendant "Free of charge."
    Attendant "За счет заведения."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:650
translate spanish hwb_s02_cee675b3:

    # Marina "Really?"
    Marina "Серьезно?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:672
translate spanish hwb_s02_bf05ecbb:

    # "Marina lights up like a firecracker and bounces up and down like she's a kid again."
    "Marina se ilumina como un petardo y brinca arriba y abajo como si fuera una niña otra vez."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:674
translate spanish hwb_s02_e79aa9bd:

    # Attendant "Yup!"
    Attendant "Ага!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:678
translate spanish hwb_s02_1f65aca9:

    # Marina "Oh wow, thanks, mister!"
    Marina "Ого, вау, спасибо вам, мистер!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:685
translate spanish hwb_s02_17c2ce74:

    # "In one swift motion, she swipes one of the remaining books off the rack so fast that I swear my eyes are skipping frames."
    "En un movimiento rápido, toma uno de los libros restantes del estante tan rápido que juro que mis ojos se saltan fotogramas."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:689
translate spanish hwb_s02_43dcc532:

    # Marina "Hey Amber, look. He gave me one for free!"
    Marina "Эй, Эмбер, смотри, он дал мне одну бесплатно!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:693
translate spanish hwb_s02_c35e3898:

    # Amber "Yeah, yeah, I see it…"
    Amber "Да, да, я вижу..."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:705
translate spanish hwb_s02_6bc0b96e:

    # "I tune out her chattering and nod as we walk out to the parking lot so we can finally get the fuel."
    "Ignoro su parloteo y asiento mientras salimos al estacionamiento para por fin conseguir el combustible."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:707
translate spanish hwb_s02_eae6fbc4:

    # "The attendant shouts one last thing, his voice fading behind the glass of the closing door."
    "El empleado grita una última cosa, su voz desvaneciéndose detrás del vidrio de la puerta que se cierra."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:711
translate spanish hwb_s02_4aec69be:

    # Attendant "Good luck on your trip!"
    Attendant "Удачи вам в путешествии!"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:713
translate spanish hwb_s02_a20cefa7:

    # "..."
    "..."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:715
translate spanish hwb_s02_f5f3b334:

    # "Desert people are weird."
    "La gente del desierto es rara."

translate spanish strings:

    # game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:3
    old "Station Attendant"
    new "Кассир"

    old "Attendant"
    new "Кассир"

    # game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:4
    old "Bandana Girl"
    new "Девушка в бандане"
# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:52
translate spanish hwb_s02_5fe56771:

    # "The drive was quiet after I turned the music on. Turning the tables on her and asking what she was doing out there seemed to throw her off."
    "El viaje fue tranquilo después de que puse la música. Preguntarle qué hacía allí pareció desconcertarla."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:145
translate spanish hwb_s02_a8b51911:

    # "Her pure, concentrated sadness melts into pure, concentrated happiness."
    "Su tristeza pura y concentrada se derrite en una felicidad pura y concentrada."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:168
translate spanish hwb_s02_72cc3eee:

    # "I spot the gas cans, and with Marina happily sipping her drink, grab one and head for the counter."
    "Veo los bidones de gasolina, y con Marina bebiendo felizmente su refresco, agarro uno y me dirijo al mostrador."

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:474
translate spanish hwb_s02_9e1e851a:

    # Attendant "Well now, looks like Sister here's been doin' her research."
    Attendant "Похоже, малая неплохо подготовилась, да?"

# game/script/hwb_s02.rpy:650
translate spanish hwb_s02_cee675b3_1:

    # Marina "Really?"
    Marina "Серьезно?"

translate spanish strings:

    # script/hwb_s02.rpy:743
    old "Driving to Marina's car"
    new "Driving to Marina's car"

